The P2P theory has found fertile ground in Greece and has inspired several people and initiatives.  

*See the [http://www.p2plab.gr/en/ P2P lab], an interdisciplinary research collective focused on the commons that is based in Ioannina, Greece. 
*The page [[Greek language]] contains rich material on P2P theory in Greek. 
*Watch three documentaries (subtitled in English) on the commons/P2P movement in Greece:
*# "[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=T5Uj-twO-zc Building Communities of Commons in Greece: A Documentary on Networks in Sarantaporo Area]." Video with more info.
*# "[http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=8iCZgZEYm0w Knowledge as a Common. Communities of production and sharing in Greece]". Video with more info.
*# A documentary on the Tzoumakers initiative of the P2P Lab to air in mid-September. Updates soon.


